WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:03.080
Let's get the bastard.

00:03.080 --> 00:04.600
Going to need you to do
something for me.

00:04.600 --> 00:05.680
Something not very nice.

00:05.680 --> 00:07.280
Chuck us your phone, I'll stick me
number in.

00:07.280 --> 00:08.400
Put it in as James, yeah?

00:08.400 --> 00:10.200
I made a friend from group.

00:10.200 --> 00:12.280
Oi, are you not worried?

00:12.280 --> 00:14.240
You can carry on working for Col
or you can quit.

00:14.240 --> 00:15.960
Those are the two people that

00:15.960 --> 00:17.440
you get to be, so choose.

00:17.440 --> 00:20.760
Anything that puts Owen at harm's
way, I'll leave.

00:20.760 --> 00:23.840
What if I can get the Maliks
out the way for you?

00:23.840 --> 00:26.280
Phone us in a tip-off, I hard stop
them.

00:26.280 --> 00:28.040
You put the gear in the Maliks' car.

00:28.040 --> 00:29.120
Why?

00:29.120 --> 00:31.000
Cos I work for Col McHugh.

00:31.000 --> 00:33.040
I always have.

01:15.600 --> 01:17.960
You going to say something?

01:20.920 --> 01:23.760
I don't always know what to say,
I'm not like you.

01:30.640 --> 01:33.200
How did you end up working for him?

01:33.200 --> 01:34.440
Don't matter.

01:35.920 --> 01:38.040
I am where I am.

01:43.640 --> 01:46.480
I wanted to be you.

01:46.480 --> 01:47.920
When I was starting out, me friends

01:47.920 --> 01:49.320
would say, "What you doing, Est?"

01:49.320 --> 01:50.840
And I said, "No, you don't get it.

01:50.840 --> 01:52.920
"There's this DI, she's killing
it."

01:54.640 --> 01:56.680
And the whole time, you were on the
take.

01:56.680 --> 01:57.920
It's not like that.

01:57.920 --> 02:00.080
What is it like, then?

02:00.080 --> 02:02.280
It weren't a one-way street.

02:02.280 --> 02:04.480
He gave me a lot of intel.

02:04.480 --> 02:07.440
Most of my big cases turned on
something he gave me.

02:09.520 --> 02:12.680
If it's so mutual, why does he have
to pay you?

02:12.680 --> 02:14.240
Oh, look, does it matter?

02:14.240 --> 02:15.920
It's over, I'm out.

02:15.920 --> 02:17.800
Since I caught you this morning?

02:17.800 --> 02:20.720
No, since before that.

02:20.720 --> 02:23.000
I'm telling you, it's over.

02:23.000 --> 02:25.600
I'm going to bring him in but it
has to be my way.

02:25.600 --> 02:27.080
And he cannot know.

02:27.080 --> 02:29.440
No, don't do that.

02:29.440 --> 02:31.800
Don't treat me like I'm an idiot,
you know I'm not.

02:31.800 --> 02:33.680
No, I know, I know how it sounds

02:33.680 --> 02:35.360
but I promise you I'm not lying.

02:35.360 --> 02:36.920
It's over, Esther.

02:41.160 --> 02:43.560
You know I have to tell Sandy.

02:43.560 --> 02:45.800
Grass?  Don't you dare.

02:51.200 --> 02:52.760
OK, I won't tell her.

02:53.800 --> 02:56.480
If you do tell her yourself, it's
the best way.

02:56.480 --> 02:57.880
I can't.

02:57.880 --> 03:00.480
If I betray him, he will come for
me, for me family.

03:00.480 --> 03:03.240
Not if he's inside.

03:03.240 --> 03:06.480
Well, I'm sorry, if you don't,
I have to.

03:06.480 --> 03:09.400
Please, let me make this right.

03:09.400 --> 03:11.560
Let me finish what I have started
here.

03:11.560 --> 03:13.560
Well, finish what? You've done what
you've done.

03:13.560 --> 03:15.720
I won't lie for you, I can't, it's
wrong.

03:15.720 --> 03:18.760
Oh, it's as simple as that, is it?
Yeah...

03:18.760 --> 03:20.640
..it is.

03:23.920 --> 03:26.000
You're a good copper.

03:30.480 --> 03:32.400
How would you know?

03:47.160 --> 03:49.640
Lou, what you doing?
You're going to wake Owen.

03:51.480 --> 03:53.080
Lou?

03:54.680 --> 03:55.920
What's happened?  It's over.

03:55.920 --> 03:58.080
We have to get all of this out of
the house.

03:58.080 --> 03:59.400
What do you mean, over?

03:59.400 --> 04:01.360
Esther caught me doing something for
Col

04:01.360 --> 04:03.840
and she's going to Sandy.

04:03.840 --> 04:07.360
They're going to search the house,
so we have to get rid of everything.

04:08.520 --> 04:09.760
What'll happen?

04:09.760 --> 04:11.520
Erm, well, I'll deny everything.

04:11.520 --> 04:14.680
Cos I can't co-operate, Col would
find out.

04:14.680 --> 04:16.760
Well, I'll take it all.

04:16.760 --> 04:18.760
I'll burn it if I have to.

04:29.560 --> 04:31.440
So it is over, then?

04:32.440 --> 04:34.960
I'm no use to Col if I get caught,
am I?

04:37.320 --> 04:38.920
So resign.

04:38.920 --> 04:41.120
Do it tomorrow...

04:41.120 --> 04:42.640
..before anything happens.

04:42.640 --> 04:44.440
You were going to anyway.

04:44.440 --> 04:45.960
I know it's not the end that you

04:45.960 --> 04:47.680
wanted, but it's an end.

04:47.680 --> 04:49.880
This is the best we could've hoped
for.

04:49.880 --> 04:51.840
Is it?  Yeah.

04:53.000 --> 04:54.360
You know, nothing else matters.

04:54.360 --> 04:55.920
None of it's your problem.

04:58.040 --> 05:00.440
We'll be free.

05:00.440 --> 05:01.680
Yeah?

05:05.360 --> 05:08.280
After all this, we get to walk away.

05:11.280 --> 05:13.240
Come on, come down.

05:13.240 --> 05:15.560
I'll sort the money later.

05:38.640 --> 05:40.280
How you feeling?

05:40.280 --> 05:41.880
Condemned.

05:49.200 --> 05:51.840
You've just got to get through
this part.  Mm-hm.

06:23.880 --> 06:25.520
There you go.

06:25.520 --> 06:27.160
Cheers.

06:40.520 --> 06:42.600
Morning, Ma'am.

07:06.000 --> 07:09.240
OFFICE CHATTER

07:15.280 --> 07:17.920
PHONE RINGS

07:28.000 --> 07:29.600
Morning.  Morning, morning.

07:33.280 --> 07:34.520
PHONE RINGS

07:37.960 --> 07:39.560
VOICEMAIL:  Hi, you're through to

07:39.560 --> 07:42.760
Esther  Okoye.  Leave me a message
and I'll get back to you.  Argh.

07:44.160 --> 07:45.960
Est, call me back,

07:45.960 --> 07:47.840
it's  not what you think.

07:47.840 --> 07:49.840
You're going to want to hear this.

08:14.120 --> 08:15.720
What are you playing at?

08:15.720 --> 08:17.160
I need to talk to you.

08:17.160 --> 08:18.560
Jesus Christ, not here.

08:18.560 --> 08:20.480
Col, you have to let me in!

08:38.720 --> 08:40.280
Listen to me, we've got no time.

08:40.280 --> 08:41.720
I've just come from the station and

08:41.720 --> 08:43.400
I've seen something I weren't meant
to.

08:43.400 --> 08:45.840
There's a taskforce, you're the
target.

08:45.840 --> 08:48.280
I'm not on it, they have
deliberately kept me from it.

08:48.280 --> 08:49.840
They know about us.

08:49.840 --> 08:52.520
They have to. Why else would they
freeze me out?

08:52.520 --> 08:56.120
Right.  No,  don't. They could've
turned someone.

08:56.120 --> 08:57.520
Right. What do they have?

08:57.520 --> 08:59.720
I don't know. But enough for a
warrant to search the house.

08:59.720 --> 09:01.280
When?  No idea.

09:01.280 --> 09:02.600
I came as soon as I saw. They could

09:02.600 --> 09:04.400
be on their way to you right now,
for all I know.

09:04.400 --> 09:06.160
You need to clear-out the house out
now.

09:07.880 --> 09:09.680
Well, you know I don't keep anything

09:09.680 --> 09:11.080
in the house, you know that.

09:11.080 --> 09:13.000
What's in your safe? Just your
cufflinks?

09:15.680 --> 09:17.760
Everything's encrypted.

09:17.760 --> 09:20.720
You want to take that chance?

09:20.720 --> 09:23.680
Be sure and clear-out the house and
do it now.

09:35.400 --> 09:36.680
KNOCKS ON DOOR

09:36.680 --> 09:38.200
Yep?

09:40.600 --> 09:42.480
Ma'am, can I have a word?

09:59.240 --> 10:01.040
I won't be a minute, DC Okoye,

10:01.040 --> 10:04.080
I just need to send this.

10:05.080 --> 10:06.800
You all right?

10:06.800 --> 10:08.120
Yes, Ma'am.

10:12.160 --> 10:13.880
Come on, Col.

10:22.920 --> 10:24.600
PHONE RINGS

10:31.480 --> 10:33.920
Sorry,  Ma'am, can I, erm...?

10:33.920 --> 10:35.440
Sure.

10:45.320 --> 10:46.520
Esther, are you there?

10:46.520 --> 10:48.200
You can't change my mind.

10:48.200 --> 10:49.520
No, this, this isn't about last

10:49.520 --> 10:52.000
night, this is about Col McHugh.
Do you want to bring him in?

10:52.000 --> 10:53.320
I'm not playing your games, Lou.

10:53.320 --> 10:54.640
No, this ain't a game.

10:54.640 --> 10:56.760
He's leaving his house to dispose of
evidence,

10:56.760 --> 10:58.560
stuff you could use to nail him.

10:58.560 --> 11:00.360
Well, why don't you bring him in?

11:00.360 --> 11:01.800
You know I can't.

11:01.800 --> 11:04.280
You just say it's from a source
and we'll deal with it later.

11:07.040 --> 11:09.120
Where is he?

11:09.120 --> 11:10.600
He hasn't come out yet.

11:10.600 --> 11:12.360
Well, what exactly is he carrying?

11:12.360 --> 11:16.240
I'm pretty sure it's computer stuff,
like hard drives.

11:16.240 --> 11:18.520
You're "Pretty sure"? Forget it.

11:24.680 --> 11:26.320
PHONE RINGS

11:28.080 --> 11:30.440
You  said you wanted to make a
difference.

11:30.440 --> 11:31.960
Well, here's your opportunity.

11:31.960 --> 11:34.000
I'm parked-up half a mile from his
house.

11:34.000 --> 11:36.000
There's only one road that
goes in or out.

11:37.120 --> 11:38.640
I'm betting he's leaving soon

11:38.640 --> 11:40.120
and I'm betting he's carrying summat

11:40.120 --> 11:42.200
on him that we could use to bring
him down.

11:44.840 --> 11:46.760
You want me to trust you?

11:46.760 --> 11:49.280
Look, if I'm wrong, all that happens
is you look daft.

11:49.280 --> 11:52.240
But if I'm right, you get to bring
down Col McHugh today.

11:52.240 --> 11:55.880
We'll decide what to do about me
later.

11:55.880 --> 11:58.200
Esther, you're only going to get one
chance at this.

11:58.200 --> 11:59.600
Get over here now!

12:17.760 --> 12:19.200
Esther?

12:21.360 --> 12:23.840
Sorry, Ma'am. It were a source.

12:23.840 --> 12:25.840
OK. Do you want to have that chat?

12:25.840 --> 12:28.280
Erm, it's nothing, it'll wait.

12:28.280 --> 12:30.480
Well, it's nothing or it'll wait?

12:30.480 --> 12:32.240
I really need to chase this up.

12:32.240 --> 12:35.000
It could be relevant to the
taskforce.

12:35.000 --> 12:36.280
Fine.

12:36.280 --> 12:37.920
Off you go.

12:47.120 --> 12:49.600
It's the old Church Road,
right?

12:49.600 --> 12:50.760
Are you close?

12:50.760 --> 12:53.480
I'm coming towards you now.
Any sign?

12:57.200 --> 12:58.600
Not yet.

12:59.760 --> 13:01.640
Oh, come on.

13:30.600 --> 13:32.160
Just give him a bit more time.

13:35.360 --> 13:37.400
No, I'm heading back.

13:38.480 --> 13:39.960
There he is.

13:43.160 --> 13:45.200
Everything by the book from here on
out.

13:45.200 --> 13:46.640
I'll go back to the station.

13:46.640 --> 13:48.560
Go get him, Est.

14:12.200 --> 14:14.480
ESTHER ON PHONE: In a silver
Mercedes.

14:14.480 --> 14:17.120
Foxtrot, golf, 16, November,
uniform, hotel.

14:17.120 --> 14:18.680
No passengers visible.

14:20.280 --> 14:22.760
You'll never guess who Esther's
tailing.

14:22.760 --> 14:24.360
It's Col McHugh.

14:24.360 --> 14:26.640
Supposedly, he's moving some
incriminating evidence,

14:26.640 --> 14:27.880
she's had some intel.

14:27.880 --> 14:29.400
You're kidding. Is she on her own?

14:29.400 --> 14:30.960
At the moment, yeah.

14:30.960 --> 14:32.400
We're getting units out to her.

14:32.400 --> 14:35.440
She's not to pull him till she's got
backup.

14:35.440 --> 14:37.920
SANDY ON SPEAKER:  Maintain contact,
at a distance.

14:37.920 --> 14:40.840
Let's just see where he gets to.
Yes, Ma'am.

14:47.480 --> 14:49.960
He's barely pushing the speed limit.

14:49.960 --> 14:51.640
Proper careful.

14:51.640 --> 14:53.960
Yeah well, you would be if you had
something on you.

14:53.960 --> 14:56.400
Stay far back as you can,
DC Okoye.

15:08.480 --> 15:11.280
Just turned onto Green Lane.

15:11.280 --> 15:13.120
Heading for the A658.

15:14.800 --> 15:16.680
That's towards Bradford Airport.

15:21.360 --> 15:22.680
Wait, hold up.

15:22.680 --> 15:25.000
What? What's happened?

15:25.000 --> 15:26.880
He's pulling into a petrol station.

15:55.240 --> 15:57.680
He's getting a bag out the boot.

15:57.680 --> 16:01.080
Large holdall, looks heavy.

16:01.080 --> 16:03.200
Could be a handover.  Or getting rid.

16:07.040 --> 16:09.000
POLICE RADIO: With you in two
minutes. Over.

16:09.000 --> 16:10.800
Shall I go now?

16:10.800 --> 16:12.320
SANDY:  Uniform there?

16:12.320 --> 16:13.520
Almost.

16:13.520 --> 16:15.600
No, no, no, You wait for them.

16:17.960 --> 16:19.760
Sorry, Ma'am, he's going inside.

16:19.760 --> 16:20.840
I'll lose sight of bag.

16:20.840 --> 16:22.680
SANDY:  DC Okoye!

16:22.680 --> 16:24.360
Col McHugh!

16:24.360 --> 16:27.440
DC Esther Okoye,
Central Yorkshire Police.

16:29.400 --> 16:31.000
I have reasonable grounds to suspect

16:31.000 --> 16:33.600
you may be carrying stolen
or prohibited articles.

16:37.560 --> 16:40.840
You'll have to ask my lawyer about
that.

16:40.840 --> 16:43.080
Erm, Mr McHugh...

16:43.080 --> 16:45.560
..under Section One of the Police
and Criminal Evidence Act

16:45.560 --> 16:47.400
of 1984, I'm legally permitted to

16:47.400 --> 16:50.520
carry out a stop and search.

16:50.520 --> 16:52.880
I can also use reasonable force,
should you resist,

16:52.880 --> 16:55.560
which could lead to your arrest.

16:55.560 --> 16:58.200
You will be entitled to a copy of
the search record.

16:58.200 --> 16:59.680
I'll give you a reference number.

17:01.960 --> 17:03.880
Ma'am.

17:06.480 --> 17:08.320
May I look inside your bag, please?

17:17.320 --> 17:19.600
Could you open it for me, please?

18:00.440 --> 18:02.000
SANDY:  What is it?

18:03.120 --> 18:04.480
It's um...

18:05.520 --> 18:06.760
..nothing.

18:07.960 --> 18:09.560
What do you mean, "nothing"?

18:09.560 --> 18:11.280
It's just...

18:11.280 --> 18:14.760
..office stuff, some printer paper.

18:14.760 --> 18:16.560
Packs of Post-It notes.

18:16.560 --> 18:19.360
Post-Its?  Is he messing with us?

18:36.720 --> 18:39.400
Don't worry about the reference
number, hmm.

18:46.760 --> 18:48.440
DOORBELL RINGS

18:57.920 --> 18:59.760
Busy?

19:16.920 --> 19:19.680
You sure I shouldn't have me chair?

19:19.680 --> 19:21.760
No, you won't need it.

19:25.520 --> 19:27.880
You won't need that, either.

19:27.880 --> 19:29.920
No phones today.

19:29.920 --> 19:31.640
They only tell you what to do.

19:31.640 --> 19:35.440
Leave it. Me and you are going
off grid, bro.

19:35.440 --> 19:37.120
I can't leave it.

19:37.120 --> 19:38.560
My parents would freak.

19:38.560 --> 19:40.400
What are you, ten?

19:42.200 --> 19:43.800
I can turn it off.

19:50.040 --> 19:51.680
Done.

19:51.680 --> 19:53.560
Go on, then.

19:53.560 --> 19:57.120
Come on then, bro, let's go on your
big adventure.

19:57.120 --> 19:58.680
Better not be shit, though.

20:07.400 --> 20:08.960
OWEN ON VOICEMAIL:  Hello?

20:08.960 --> 20:10.440
Hello?

20:10.440 --> 20:12.400
OK, old voicemail joke.

20:12.400 --> 20:14.440
But admit it, I got you.

20:14.440 --> 20:16.080
It's Owen, leave a message.

20:17.720 --> 20:19.400
Tell them to get a wriggle on,
yeah?

20:19.400 --> 20:20.960
We're going to lift by Monday.

20:20.960 --> 20:22.520
All right, I'll be two minutes.

20:22.520 --> 20:24.360
OK, guys, we need to speed up, yeah?

20:26.000 --> 20:27.640
See you.

20:34.560 --> 20:37.360
PHONE VIBRATES

20:37.360 --> 20:39.760
PHONE:  One new message.

20:39.760 --> 20:42.360
LOU: Ceri, I'm  so sorry.

20:42.360 --> 20:44.760
I tried to set Col up and he knows,

20:44.760 --> 20:46.400
so don't come home.

20:46.400 --> 20:48.000
He might have people watching the
house.

20:48.000 --> 20:49.880
I'm going to find Owen, I'm going to
sort it.

20:49.880 --> 20:52.280
I'm so sorry.
It'll be OK.

21:16.320 --> 21:17.760
Owen?

21:22.040 --> 21:24.200
Owen, are you here, love?

21:54.760 --> 21:56.160
OWEN ON VOICEMAIL:  Hello?

21:56.160 --> 21:57.560
Owen, Owen, love.

21:57.560 --> 21:59.960
Hello? OK, old voicemail joke.

21:59.960 --> 22:02.240
But admit it, I got you.

22:02.240 --> 22:04.360
It's Owen, leave a message.

22:04.360 --> 22:05.920
Owen, love, you've got to call me

22:05.920 --> 22:09.040
back, it's important, OK? As soon
as.

22:09.040 --> 22:11.000
I love you. Bye.

22:42.880 --> 22:45.520
PHONE VIBRATES

22:51.640 --> 22:52.920
Yes?

22:52.920 --> 22:54.800
Your lad's safe - for now.

22:54.800 --> 22:56.320
I don't believe you.

22:56.320 --> 22:58.240
Yeah, you do.

22:58.240 --> 22:59.640
The farm.

22:59.640 --> 23:01.280
Half an hour.

23:01.280 --> 23:02.760
Alone...

23:02.760 --> 23:04.520
..or we drown him.

23:21.760 --> 23:23.160
What's up with you?

23:23.160 --> 23:25.400
I thought you said it wasn't far?
It's not.

23:25.400 --> 23:27.240
I use the chair for a reason.

23:31.520 --> 23:33.080
Where are we going?

23:33.080 --> 23:34.880
A bit further down here.

23:34.880 --> 23:36.280
We'll be well away, trust me,

23:36.280 --> 23:38.520
it's worth it.  All right.

23:38.520 --> 23:40.200
Give us a drag of that.

23:40.200 --> 23:42.400
Here you are.

23:42.400 --> 23:44.600
Nice one, mate.  It's all right.

24:03.000 --> 24:05.320
Come on, you coward! Open the gate!

24:05.320 --> 24:08.160
Come on! Come out!

24:12.040 --> 24:13.800
What's the matter with you?

24:13.800 --> 24:15.120
You really want to be seen here?

24:15.120 --> 24:16.680
Is she in there?

24:16.680 --> 24:17.760
Lou?

24:17.760 --> 24:19.200
No, of course not.

24:19.200 --> 24:21.400
If he hurts her, Alma,
I'll kill him.

24:22.880 --> 24:24.200
You'll do nothing. I don't know

24:24.200 --> 24:25.640
where Col is, he doesn't tell me.

24:25.640 --> 24:27.320
So get back in your truck.

24:27.320 --> 24:28.840
You came, you shouted, you can tell

24:28.840 --> 24:31.280
yourself you did something, maybe it
helps you.

24:49.640 --> 24:51.120
Told you it were good.

24:53.960 --> 24:55.200
You don't like it?

24:56.200 --> 24:57.240
I do.

24:58.280 --> 25:01.840
Bit of a weird place for your dad
to take a little kid, though.

25:01.840 --> 25:03.200
Yeah!

25:03.200 --> 25:05.720
But I were a proper mentalist.

25:05.720 --> 25:09.000
Tasmanian Devil, he used to call me.

25:09.000 --> 25:11.560
And sometimes it'd get so bad, he'd

25:11.560 --> 25:13.520
just chuck us in car and take us

25:13.520 --> 25:15.280
somewhere far away from anyone.

25:15.280 --> 25:16.920
Let me run wild.

25:19.520 --> 25:22.120
Funny thing is though...

25:22.120 --> 25:25.400
..whenever he brought me here...

25:25.400 --> 25:27.200
..I'd just be chill.

25:34.080 --> 25:36.680
I'm not, erm...

25:37.720 --> 25:39.440
I think I knew.

25:39.440 --> 25:40.840
It's OK.

25:40.840 --> 25:42.200
Don't feel embarrassed.

25:43.520 --> 25:45.360
Why would I be embarrassed?

25:47.600 --> 25:49.400
PHONE PINGS

25:51.600 --> 25:53.520
I  thought you said no phones.

25:53.520 --> 25:55.280
I thought it were off.

25:59.600 --> 26:01.160
It's excruciatingly obvious that

26:01.160 --> 26:04.200
it's your girlfriend, which is
completely fine.

26:05.920 --> 26:08.920
Did you think I thought someone
like you could be miraculously

26:08.920 --> 26:10.920
