26:15.400 --> 26:17.800
What were that?

26:17.800 --> 26:19.600
You want to capture the exquisite

26:19.600 --> 26:21.480
awkwardness of this moment forever?

26:23.200 --> 26:25.280
Don't know.

26:25.280 --> 26:27.120
Summat people do.

27:03.920 --> 27:06.360
Argh!

27:06.360 --> 27:08.080
SHE COUGHS

27:12.800 --> 27:14.440
You see that?

27:15.880 --> 27:17.400
You  see it, Slack?

27:48.960 --> 27:51.160
Where's Owen?

27:51.160 --> 27:52.880
What have you done with him?

27:52.880 --> 27:55.640
Col, where is my son?

27:55.640 --> 27:58.120
You tried to set me up this morning.

27:58.120 --> 28:00.720
You've been working against me
for a wee while now.

28:04.440 --> 28:07.440
Has Owen ever shown you a picture of
his wee friend James?

28:11.520 --> 28:13.240
That's him.

28:15.600 --> 28:18.880
Apparently, you and Ceri have been
arguing for years now about a man.

28:23.520 --> 28:25.600
Owen doesn't know his name but...

28:25.600 --> 28:27.200
..recently you've been talking

28:27.200 --> 28:29.840
about stabbing him in the back,
getting rid of him.

28:32.880 --> 28:34.000
He, he doesn't know.

28:34.000 --> 28:36.520
He thinks he's having a nice
day out with his,

28:36.520 --> 28:39.160
with his pal down by the water.

28:39.160 --> 28:40.960
Please, Col.

28:40.960 --> 28:43.560
Maybe that doesn't have to change.
Maybe he doesn't have to get hurt.

28:45.360 --> 28:47.400
So long as we don't have any more
lies.

28:47.400 --> 28:49.760
I have no more to tell.
No, good, good.

28:49.760 --> 28:51.200
So, why?

28:54.840 --> 28:57.480
I wanted to bring you down.

28:57.480 --> 28:59.120
Really?

29:01.680 --> 29:03.640
I see. And why is that?

29:07.760 --> 29:09.080
I can't explain it.

29:09.080 --> 29:10.720
Well, try and do better.

29:10.720 --> 29:12.080
OK.

29:13.320 --> 29:15.840
The night that we nearly
lost Owen...

29:16.800 --> 29:18.680
..I asked for him to be saved.

29:18.680 --> 29:20.280
And then he was saved.

29:20.280 --> 29:22.160
And when I went back to work...

29:22.160 --> 29:24.080
..I realised that my part of the

29:24.080 --> 29:26.280
deal was stopping you.

29:27.800 --> 29:29.040
Why?

29:31.000 --> 29:32.520
Because it's wrong.

29:32.520 --> 29:33.920
Oh, ha-ha.

29:33.920 --> 29:36.120
You  hear that, Bulge?

29:36.120 --> 29:37.680
"Because it's wrong."

29:37.680 --> 29:39.440
Has this only just occurred?

29:39.440 --> 29:41.520
Yeah.

29:41.520 --> 29:43.600
Oh, no.

29:43.600 --> 29:45.800
Oh, no.

29:45.800 --> 29:48.000
You found God?  No, it's not like
that.

29:48.000 --> 29:49.160
He found you?

29:49.160 --> 29:51.920
No, I'm too canny for him,
he can't track me down.

29:53.800 --> 29:55.720
I don't know what to tell you, Col.

29:58.840 --> 30:00.480
Now, here's the question.

30:03.280 --> 30:06.080
Why didn't you just walk away?

30:06.080 --> 30:08.240
Because you're the problem.

30:08.240 --> 30:10.320
I'm to blame for you.

30:10.320 --> 30:12.720
If it wasn't for you...
Oh, I'm the problem?!

30:12.720 --> 30:14.360
I'm the problem?

30:14.360 --> 30:15.640
You're a drug dealer.

30:15.640 --> 30:17.320
I give people something they want,

30:17.320 --> 30:19.880
something they choose to buy freely,
Lou.

30:19.880 --> 30:23.200
The drugs you sell ruin people's
lives, you know that.

30:23.200 --> 30:25.040
Oh, God! If only people choose a

30:25.040 --> 30:27.920
more respectable way of ruining
themselves, eh, Bulge?

30:27.920 --> 30:30.480
Like drink and fags, and takeaways,
and betting,

30:30.480 --> 30:32.640
and anything else with a tax code.

30:32.640 --> 30:34.760
Oh, you can't compare the two.
Oh, can I not?

30:34.760 --> 30:37.080
My da never broke the law for his
fix.

30:37.080 --> 30:39.800
Every last drop of alcohol,
legally obtained.

30:39.800 --> 30:43.120
And that was such a great comfort to
us.

30:43.120 --> 30:46.360
When he shat himself at Christmas
dinner.

30:46.360 --> 30:50.320
When he threw a pan of hot oil
over my mother.

30:50.320 --> 30:52.840
When he died at
54 years old,

30:52.840 --> 30:55.920
all small and yellow, with a wee
pregnant tummy.

30:55.920 --> 30:57.800
If it's bad for you but feels good,

30:57.800 --> 31:00.800
people are going to find
a way to do it.

31:00.800 --> 31:03.720
Legal, illegal, that's just the
prevailing wind.

31:03.720 --> 31:06.880
It has fuck all to do with right
and wrong.

31:06.880 --> 31:08.400
Chemicals don't have morals.

31:08.400 --> 31:11.040
Oh, Jesus, don't try and justify
what you do.

31:11.040 --> 31:12.880
Why not? Why not?

31:12.880 --> 31:14.320
You know how many heroin addicts

31:14.320 --> 31:16.440
there were in Britain in the 1960s?
Around 300.

31:16.440 --> 31:19.000
And do you know where they got their
gear from? Do you know that?

31:19.000 --> 31:22.480
Boots.
Boots, The Chemist, on prescription.

31:24.120 --> 31:26.800
And then the politics changed
and well, here we are.

31:26.800 --> 31:28.360
But all of this was a choice, Lou.

31:28.360 --> 31:30.520
What about all the people
that you hurt?

31:30.520 --> 31:33.080
You don't even know half
the stuff you do!

31:33.080 --> 31:34.680
We did all this together.

31:34.680 --> 31:36.200
No! If I'd never met you...

31:36.200 --> 31:38.520
You were looking for me, just like I
was looking for you.

31:38.520 --> 31:40.840
We're exactly the same.

31:40.840 --> 31:42.920
We're the same.

31:42.920 --> 31:45.360
We want to skip a few rungs
together, don't we?

31:45.360 --> 31:48.000
We want to fucking get somewhere,
and fucking do something.

31:48.000 --> 31:50.640
And all their rules out there are a
fucking joke to us.

31:50.640 --> 31:52.280
But I know that.

31:52.280 --> 31:56.160
I know who I am and so does everyone
else around me.

31:56.160 --> 31:58.640
But you, you're a fucking liar!

31:59.720 --> 32:01.520
You are a liar!

32:03.320 --> 32:05.400
You lie to every person around you!

32:05.400 --> 32:07.720
Me, Ceri, Owen, yourself!

32:07.720 --> 32:10.520
You're even lying right now!

32:10.520 --> 32:13.080
You are not as honest as you
think you are, Col.

32:13.080 --> 32:14.560
My da held me underwater once.

32:14.560 --> 32:16.320
Didn't he, Bulge? My da.

32:17.400 --> 32:19.200
Jesus Christ, the fear, the panic.

32:19.200 --> 32:21.320
Now imagine...

32:21.320 --> 32:23.200
..imagine Owen just

32:23.200 --> 32:26.320
looking up at his pal, James...

32:26.320 --> 32:28.600
..and just thinking, "Why, for
God's sake? Don't do this to me."

32:28.600 --> 32:31.200
In fact, no, I wouldn't let that
happen, that wouldn't be fair.

32:31.200 --> 32:34.520
I'd get him say it was because of
you, first, so at least he'd know.

32:34.520 --> 32:35.600
No.

32:35.600 --> 32:37.440
You fucking touch him and I'll kill
you!

32:37.440 --> 32:39.120
And if I don't, Ceri will rip your
eyes out!

32:39.120 --> 32:40.800
That's what you're going to think
now

32:40.800 --> 32:42.640
but most people, when someone they
love gets hurt

32:42.640 --> 32:44.120
and it's their fault, it rips the

32:44.120 --> 32:45.880
fight out of them, it breaks you.

32:48.960 --> 32:50.800
Is that what happened to you?

32:52.200 --> 32:55.320
Is that what happened to you, when
Aoife killed herself with your gear?

33:00.880 --> 33:02.120
WHISPERS:  Don't.

33:02.120 --> 33:03.840
Or what, you'll kill me again?

33:03.840 --> 33:06.080
You'll kill me twice?

33:06.080 --> 33:10.440
You supplied the drugs that your
daughter used to kill herself.

33:11.800 --> 33:13.640
You know that.

33:13.640 --> 33:16.040
She knew that, the whole world knows
that!

33:16.040 --> 33:17.520
But I'll bet you a tenner I'm

33:17.520 --> 33:19.240
the first one to say it out-loud.
Don't you...

33:19.240 --> 33:21.200
The truth,  you want the truth?  Don't
you use her name.

33:21.200 --> 33:22.960
No-one talks about Aoife

33:22.960 --> 33:25.920
because everyone knows that she
fucking hated you.

33:25.920 --> 33:28.600
And she used your drugs to end her
life.

33:28.600 --> 33:31.640
But chemicals don't have morals.
Bulgey.

33:33.000 --> 33:34.480
"You know who you are"?

33:34.480 --> 33:36.480
THAT is who you are, Col!

33:36.480 --> 33:38.800
And when I'm gone, there'll be
no-one else to tell you.

33:43.000 --> 33:45.280
No more lies, I promise.

33:45.280 --> 33:47.040
I promise.

33:50.560 --> 33:53.440
Oh, go on, just get it over with,
I haven't got all day.

33:54.360 --> 33:55.960
SHE SNIFFS

33:58.200 --> 34:00.120
Argh!

34:01.640 --> 34:03.440
Argh!

34:19.480 --> 34:21.240
Go home.

34:23.640 --> 34:25.600
Donal will bring Owen back unharmed.

34:25.600 --> 34:28.720
And this is the last time
we see each other.

34:28.720 --> 34:30.400
One fucking chance.

34:31.880 --> 34:35.080
Ever come after me again, Lou,
everything changes.

35:01.840 --> 35:03.560
PHONE PINGS

35:08.360 --> 35:10.240
Oh.

35:13.400 --> 35:16.680
I  can't tell whether that's good
news or bad.

35:16.680 --> 35:19.040
It's good news.

35:19.040 --> 35:20.760
But we should probably head back.

35:21.920 --> 35:23.560
After...

35:23.560 --> 35:25.080
..a swim.

35:25.080 --> 35:26.920
Yeah?

35:26.920 --> 35:28.400
Come on.

35:32.080 --> 35:35.000
Right. If you want to have a
look at me cock,

35:35.000 --> 35:36.800
do it now...

35:36.800 --> 35:38.680
..and not when I come out. Yeah?

35:41.480 --> 35:43.200
OK.

35:48.160 --> 35:50.280
Woohoo!

35:51.560 --> 35:54.440
Argh!

35:54.440 --> 35:56.280
Come on!

35:59.160 --> 36:00.880
Come on, mate!

36:00.880 --> 36:02.360
What are you waiting for?

36:05.800 --> 36:07.320
Oh.

36:09.600 --> 36:11.760
Woo!

36:15.960 --> 36:17.480
OWEN ON VOICEMAIL:  Hello?

36:17.480 --> 36:19.480
Hello?

36:19.480 --> 36:21.120
OK, old voicemail joke

36:21.120 --> 36:23.000
but admit it, I got you.

36:23.000 --> 36:24.920
It's Owen, leave a message.

36:27.520 --> 36:29.080
CERI:  Lou, what's happened?

36:29.080 --> 36:30.440
Is Owen OK?

36:30.440 --> 36:33.040
Yeah, everything's OK.
Just come home.

36:33.040 --> 36:35.120
Owen?

36:35.120 --> 36:37.840
CERI:  What's going on?
Are you all right?

36:37.840 --> 36:39.560
Lou?

36:39.560 --> 36:41.640
I'll explain, just come home.

37:06.840 --> 37:08.720
Thanks for an...

37:08.720 --> 37:12.880
..odd and confusing and
hypothermia-y day.

37:12.880 --> 37:15.640
Yeah, look, mate...

37:15.640 --> 37:18.120
..I'm sorry about the whole...
Like I said...

37:19.560 --> 37:21.200
..it's cool.

37:32.240 --> 37:34.040
James...

37:35.400 --> 37:37.520
..if you don't want that, then...

37:38.760 --> 37:40.640
..what are we doing?

37:41.920 --> 37:45.200
Is this just like a field trip
version of the group?

37:47.840 --> 37:51.280
That's fine, by the way.

37:51.280 --> 37:54.000
It's just nice to have some
sort of road map.

37:57.480 --> 37:58.880
I don't know.

38:01.720 --> 38:03.400
It's...

38:05.200 --> 38:07.400
..it's just good to talk to someone,
in't it?

38:11.800 --> 38:13.520
See you at Sad Bastards Group?

38:41.080 --> 38:43.240
LOU ON VOICEMAIL: Owen, love, you've
got to call me back,

38:43.240 --> 38:45.480
it's important. OK?
As soon as.

38:45.480 --> 38:46.960
I love you.

38:46.960 --> 38:48.520
Bye.

38:50.040 --> 38:51.680
Mum?

38:55.960 --> 38:57.720
What's this voicemail about?

39:01.520 --> 39:03.200
Mum?

39:05.480 --> 39:07.120
Tell me what's going on?

39:07.120 --> 39:08.520
Nothing.

39:08.520 --> 39:09.800
Don't matter.

39:09.800 --> 39:10.960
Everything's OK.

39:12.960 --> 39:14.920
I'm going for a shower.

39:46.480 --> 39:49.400
You're his son, aren't you?

39:49.400 --> 39:50.960
And?

39:52.360 --> 39:53.800
What were you doing with Owen?

39:53.800 --> 39:55.480
Nothing, just talking.

39:55.480 --> 39:57.360
I-I swear.

39:57.360 --> 39:59.840
He don't even know who I am, he
thinks I'm from the group.

40:01.480 --> 40:03.000
You're James?

40:05.760 --> 40:06.880
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

40:06.880 --> 40:08.680
You're fucking James!
No, no, no, no, no, no!

40:08.680 --> 40:11.560
It's done, it's done, it's over.
I swear, I swear.

40:11.560 --> 40:13.400
No harm done, yeah?

40:13.400 --> 40:15.000
I were never going to hurt him.

40:18.480 --> 40:19.960
Ah!

40:21.120 --> 40:23.160
Me da will fucking kill you!

40:26.800 --> 40:28.840
If I ever see you here again...

40:47.280 --> 40:48.960
What happened?

40:57.760 --> 40:59.440
Boss?

41:00.560 --> 41:02.520
Boss, just listen to me!

41:02.520 --> 41:04.480
Just listen to me.

41:04.480 --> 41:05.840
You can't do this!

41:06.960 --> 41:10.560
Boss, you do this, we'll
never be safe.

41:10.560 --> 41:11.720
She'll come again.

41:11.720 --> 41:13.440
What happened?

41:13.440 --> 41:14.640
Slack.

41:14.640 --> 41:17.240
She tried to stitch him up
and he let her walk!

41:19.440 --> 41:23.240
Alma, if he doesn't deal with her,
we're done.

41:23.240 --> 41:24.960
Everybody will know you can take a

41:24.960 --> 41:27.000
shot at Col McHugh, he don't fight
back.

41:27.000 --> 41:28.400
I've made my decision.

41:28.400 --> 41:30.560
It's not just you!

41:30.560 --> 41:32.200
What about your people?

41:32.200 --> 41:34.360
They go down with you!

41:34.360 --> 41:36.840
It's a fair question, Boss.

41:36.840 --> 41:39.280
I were an O'Brien man through
and through.

41:39.280 --> 41:40.800
And when you were takin' over, when

41:40.800 --> 41:43.720
I went with you, I got a lot of
grief.

41:43.720 --> 41:46.320
Traitor, all that.

41:46.320 --> 41:48.000
I threw in with you because I could

41:48.000 --> 41:49.560
see you were the right man for the
job.

41:49.560 --> 41:51.840
And I never, ever doubted that.

41:53.640 --> 41:56.080
Till now.  Bulgey, Curtis, would
you...?

42:11.840 --> 42:13.920
She tried to hurt us and you just
let her go?

42:13.920 --> 42:15.960
Make up your mind, Alma.

42:18.800 --> 42:21.320
Either you want out of this life...

42:22.520 --> 42:24.840
..or you want me to kill a woman who

42:24.840 --> 42:27.960
was sitting at our table two weeks
ago.

42:27.960 --> 42:29.920
Police officer...

42:29.920 --> 42:32.880
..a friend of 20 years, a mother to
a wee lad.

42:32.880 --> 42:34.040
You love her?

42:36.240 --> 42:38.320
Not like that, and you know it.

42:40.680 --> 42:43.840
Sometimes, I wish it was like that,
it wouldn't make you weak.

42:43.840 --> 42:45.680
What was I supposed to do?

42:45.680 --> 42:48.040
Keep us safe.

42:48.040 --> 42:50.840
But you haven't done that in a long
time.

42:50.840 --> 42:52.320
Mum!

43:00.760 --> 43:03.280
I don't get it.

43:03.280 --> 43:04.760
Why would he just...

43:05.880 --> 43:07.680
..let you go?

43:09.760 --> 43:11.720
Cos he cares about me?

43:14.520 --> 43:15.840
Have I ruined it?

43:15.840 --> 43:17.200
No.

43:17.200 --> 43:18.600
I ruined it.

43:18.600 --> 43:20.960
A long time ago.

43:20.960 --> 43:23.560
But he's not going to change his
mind, so.

43:24.760 --> 43:26.920
But it's his son.

43:26.920 --> 43:28.480
Yeah.

43:28.480 --> 43:30.240
KNOCK AT DOOR

43:30.240 --> 43:31.880
DOORBELL RINGS

43:40.560 --> 43:42.400
What was that this morning?

43:42.400 --> 43:43.800
Did you know he had nothing on him?

43:46.480 --> 43:49.560
Or maybe this whole thing were about
tying me up in your mess and making

43:49.560 --> 43:51.360
it harder for me to go to Sandy.

43:51.360 --> 43:52.920
Est, I'd never do that to you.

43:52.920 --> 43:55.800
Yeah, forgive me if I don't take
that as gospel.

43:55.800 --> 43:57.640
She's asking me all sorts now.

43:57.640 --> 43:59.240
How the tip came in, how the source

43:59.240 --> 44:01.160
knew what were going on in McHugh's
house.

44:01.160 --> 44:03.200
I've already had to lie to her.

44:03.200 --> 44:04.760
I'm sorry, I...

44:04.760 --> 44:06.720
I really thought we had a shot at
him.

44:06.720 --> 44:09.040
Well, then, what happened?

44:09.040 --> 44:12.640
I tried to smoke him out, and he saw
straight through me.

44:12.640 --> 44:14.640
And then he took Owen.

44:14.640 --> 44:16.240
What?

44:16.240 --> 44:17.760
Is he OK?

44:17.760 --> 44:19.680
Yeah he's OK, he's upstairs.

44:21.440 --> 44:24.120
Lou, we have to go in now.
You need protection, you need to

44:24.120 --> 44:26.760
make sure that your family is...
Look, he's given me one last chance.

44:26.760 --> 44:28.880
OK? He'll leave us alone if I leave
him alone.

44:28.880 --> 44:31.920
But if I breathe a word against him,
the deal is off.

44:31.920 --> 44:34.000
So you go do whatever you have to.

44:34.000 --> 44:36.280
OK? I get it, I really do.

44:36.280 --> 44:38.880
But I will deny everything, to
protect Ceri and Owen.

44:41.240 --> 44:43.720
Well, then, I'm fucked then,
aren't I?

44:45.680 --> 44:47.480
It'll be my word against yours.

44:48.640 --> 44:51.560
A two-year DC grassing on a DI.

44:51.560 --> 44:54.520
God, not just any DI.

44:54.520 --> 44:56.880
Plus, I took your dodgy tip.

44:56.880 --> 45:00.160
And I've lied to Sandy, I'm halfway
to discrediting meself.

45:09.000 --> 45:11.000
Jebem ti! How dare he?

45:12.080 --> 45:13.520
Da?

45:16.640 --> 45:18.440
Da...

45:18.440 --> 45:19.840
..I want to be there.

45:21.640 --> 45:24.360
Whoever you send,
I'm going with them.

45:25.400 --> 45:26.560
Whoever I send?

45:27.640 --> 45:29.320
Whoever I send?

45:31.360 --> 45:33.960
God forbid you fight your own
battles, Donal.

45:33.960 --> 45:35.680
Col!  What?

45:35.680 --> 45:38.880
You took the man's son, got a hiding
for it. Fair's fair.

45:38.880 --> 45:41.240
Now, if you want to keep going,
that's up to you.

45:41.240 --> 45:44.600
But judging by the state
of your wee face...

45:44.600 --> 45:46.280
..you might want to leave it be.

45:55.120 --> 45:57.160
BULGEY SPITS

45:59.280 --> 46:01.320
That your resignation, is it, Bulge?

46:04.480 --> 46:06.080
What happened to you?

46:26.280 --> 46:28.840
It's OK, Mum, it's OK.

46:28.840 --> 46:30.680
Did you even fight back?

48:03.640 --> 48:05.400
Not dead, then.

48:08.120 --> 48:11.280
It's the best possible result,
Slack.

48:11.280 --> 48:12.920
I'm touched you came to tell me.

48:12.920 --> 48:14.200
SHE SCOFFS

48:16.840 --> 48:18.600
What?

48:20.480 --> 48:22.440
He's still out there.

48:22.440 --> 48:23.840
So are you.

48:28.040 --> 48:31.320
I don't go in much for guilt,
meself.

48:32.920 --> 48:34.880
The one thing I do know about it,

48:34.880 --> 48:37.120
is it's ours and ours alone.

48:37.120 --> 48:38.680
He can't atone for you.

48:38.680 --> 48:39.840
CAT MEOWS

48:39.840 --> 48:41.680
Well, what do you want me to do?

48:41.680 --> 48:43.560
How about the right thing?

48:43.560 --> 48:45.440
I mean, if I turn myself in now,

48:45.440 --> 48:47.600
I put me family in danger.

48:47.600 --> 48:51.440
You put them in danger first time
you took his money.

48:51.440 --> 48:53.120
They've never been safe.

48:53.120 --> 48:55.560
CAT GURGLES

48:55.560 --> 48:58.360
You OK?

48:58.360 --> 49:01.320
Only usually makes that
noise when I kick it.

49:06.680 --> 49:08.360
Did you take it to the vet in the
end?

49:08.360 --> 49:09.640
Yeah, nowt doing.

49:09.640 --> 49:11.760
Do you know how much they want to
put it down?

49:11.760 --> 49:14.360
World's gone mad
if it's cheaper to keep it alive.

49:14.360 --> 49:16.000
DOG BARKS

49:16.000 --> 49:18.400
Yeah, daylight robbery.

49:18.400 --> 49:20.960
Although it barely resembles
a cat any more, Vern.

49:34.520 --> 49:36.040
I know you.

49:36.040 --> 49:37.640
You were the O'Briens' knifeman.

49:37.640 --> 49:40.400
They should've pensioned
you off years ago.

49:40.400 --> 49:42.520
Argh!

49:44.720 --> 49:46.440
Argh!

49:48.160 --> 49:49.800
Argh!

49:56.600 --> 49:58.080
Col let me go!

49:58.080 --> 50:00.840
His head's gone, mine hasn't!

50:00.840 --> 50:03.760
I knew you'd come again.

50:03.760 --> 50:05.360
Argh!

50:27.360 --> 50:29.320
Don't fucking touch me.

50:29.320 --> 50:30.480
Listen to the man.

50:30.480 --> 50:31.760
Call 999, Vernon!

50:31.760 --> 50:33.480
They'll never get here in time.

51:03.600 --> 51:05.120
You need to go.

51:07.600 --> 51:11.280
You need to leave, even my
neighbours will report a gunshot.

51:11.280 --> 51:12.760
Don't touch anything.

51:12.760 --> 51:14.480
Come on, come here.

51:21.840 --> 51:23.360
Have some of that.

51:25.080 --> 51:26.520
Rinse them again.

51:30.880 --> 51:32.440
No, use  your top.

51:32.440 --> 51:34.840
Then get rid of them clothes
when you get home.

51:34.840 --> 51:37.360
This isn't going to work, Vern.
We can but try, but you need to

51:37.360 --> 51:39.280
skedaddle - now.

51:39.280 --> 51:40.760
Well, where will you go?

51:40.760 --> 51:41.920
I've got a little bolthole in

51:41.920 --> 51:43.640
Guadalajara for just such
eventualities.

51:43.640 --> 51:45.360
The jet's fuelled and waiting.

51:45.360 --> 51:47.440
No, Vern...  Don't worry.

51:47.440 --> 51:50.280
It'll be all right, I'll spin them a
good yarn, you won't feature.

51:50.280 --> 51:51.760
I can't let you do this.

51:51.760 --> 51:53.080
I shot him, didn't I?

51:53.080 --> 51:55.720
Because of me.
Because he followed me.

51:55.720 --> 51:57.120
If I hadn't come here that day...

51:57.120 --> 51:59.080
Yeah, but you did and I'm glad.

52:01.040 --> 52:02.760
I never helped anyone before.

52:04.400 --> 52:06.120
Now, come on, piss off,

52:06.120 --> 52:08.040
you've got your family to think of.

52:08.040 --> 52:12.120
Me and my pal, we need to be alone.

52:12.120 --> 52:14.240
You're going to
go down for the gun alone.

52:14.240 --> 52:16.320
No... I'll tell 'em
I got it in a jumble sale.

52:16.320 --> 52:17.680
Zip it up.

52:17.680 --> 52:20.040
I'll come visit ya.
Will ya, bollocks.

52:20.040 --> 52:21.680
How suspicious would that look?

52:21.680 --> 52:23.440
That's it, now, come on, go...

52:24.520 --> 52:25.800
Go on.

52:27.800 --> 52:31.240
OPENS, CLOSES DOOR

52:57.720 --> 52:59.560
CAT MEOWS

53:16.480 --> 53:17.800
Oh, sod it.

53:21.080 --> 53:22.880
KNOCKS ON DOOR

53:29.360 --> 53:31.120
Er...

53:31.120 --> 53:33.040
..you might want to get out.

53:53.920 --> 53:56.440
DIAL TONE

53:56.440 --> 53:58.040
Emergency, which service?

53:58.040 --> 54:00.280
Fire, police.

54:01.760 --> 54:03.560
I'd say, send the lot.

54:03.560 --> 54:05.240
Address?

54:05.240 --> 54:10.040
Yep. 51 Drakefield Street,
Seacroft.

54:11.520 --> 54:12.840
And what's happened?

54:12.840 --> 54:14.560
Well,

54:14.560 --> 54:16.160
I've shot an intruder dead...

54:18.640 --> 54:20.240
..then set me house on fire.

54:23.840 --> 54:25.400
Err, someone's on their way.

54:25.400 --> 54:26.560
Right.

54:30.680 --> 54:34.560
That's my story
and I'm sticking to it.

54:57.960 --> 55:00.320
GLASS SHATTERS

55:00.320 --> 55:01.360
Oh.

55:11.840 --> 55:13.160
You OK?

55:15.200 --> 55:16.800
Erm, fine.

55:16.800 --> 55:18.360
Yeah?  Yeah.

55:18.360 --> 55:20.800
You want the bad news or
the good news?

55:20.800 --> 55:22.160
Um...

55:22.160 --> 55:23.680
The bad news...  Mm?

55:23.680 --> 55:25.360
..I've overcooked the pasta.

55:25.360 --> 55:27.320
The good news, there's loads left.

55:28.640 --> 55:29.920
OK.

55:29.920 --> 55:31.400
Give us that.

55:31.400 --> 55:32.840
HE CLEARS THROAT

55:35.040 --> 55:36.240
Come on...

55:38.240 --> 55:39.640
You sit down.

55:39.640 --> 55:41.080
I'll get a bowl.

55:49.880 --> 55:52.920
Give my legs a rub, will ya?
They're sore today.

55:54.600 --> 55:56.280
What's this? Spa treatment?

55:56.280 --> 55:57.600
Right, I'm next.

55:57.600 --> 55:58.880
VOICES BECOME MUFFLED

55:58.880 --> 56:00.360
Quick question for ya.

56:00.360 --> 56:03.040
Are you recovering from a serious
illness which almost killed ya?

56:03.040 --> 56:05.760
All right, maybe not,
but I am out on site every day,

56:05.760 --> 56:08.320
risking my life,
up and down wobbly ladders,

56:08.320 --> 56:11.040
dodging falling bricks,
all to provide for my family.

56:11.040 --> 56:13.640
VOICES FADE OUT

56:32.400 --> 56:34.400
SIRENS BLARE

56:43.920 --> 56:46.960
INDISTINCT CONVERSATION
